705341f-b.text:
(1)
Lafayette Avenue, north side, east from St. Felix Street to Fulton Street, showing a row of old houses, Nos. 39 to 53. The second building bears the inscription:
"Morrison Dining Saloon."
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
(2)
The same, showing only Nos. 39 to 43. No. 45 was
demolished.
May 11, 1929
P. L. Sperr
(3)
An additional view of the same block of houses, several of which have been renovated, and the "El" station on Fulton Street. Note a one-story taxpayer
occupying the site of No. 45.
May 17, 1940
P. L. Sperr

705341f-b.original_title: Brooklyn: Lafayette Avenue - St. Felix Street
